          ----eeee   Displays only the memory modules that are used with
               character devices.  This includes character drivers
               like *PR and *KI, as well as character filters.

          ----mmmm oooorrrr ----ssss
               Displays the memory summary only.

          ----pppp   The output is routed through the _m_o_r_e(U1) utility.  If
               the output of _m_a_p_m_e_m exceeds one screen, the screen
               will pause once every 23 lines.  See the _m_o_r_e(U1)
               command for additional information on the options that
               _m_o_r_e(U1) provides.  The ----pppp option is ignored if the
               output is redirected.

          ----rrrr   Displays only the memory modules that are used for disk
               access.  This includes floppy, hard disk and RAM
               logical drives.  (Ignored if ----llll or ----xxxx is specified.)

          ----tttt   The headers that are normally displayed are omitted
               from output.

          ----!!!!   Causes _m_a_p_m_e_m to ignore any default settings that are
               specified in the DDDDEEEEFFFFAAAAUUUULLLLTTTTSSSS////MMMMAAAADDDD file.  _M_a_p_m_e_m will also
               ignore any options that are specified to the left of
               the ----!!!! option.  Note that the DDDDEEEEFFFFAAAAUUUULLLLTTTTSSSS////MMMMAAAADDDD file is
               accessed even if the ----!!!! option is specified.

          ----???? oooorrrr ----hhhh
               Displays the help message.

          >>>>[>>>>] _f_i_l_e | _d_e_v_i_c_e
               By specifying a file or device, the output is sent to
               the specified file or device instead of the display.
               This is known as _r_e_d_i_r_e_c_t_e_d _o_u_t_p_u_t.  For example, the
               command mmmmaaaappppmmmmeeeemmmm >>>> ssssttttaaaatttteeee::::0000 stores the output of _m_a_p_m_e_m in
               the file SSSSTTTTAAAATTTTEEEE::::0000.  If >>>>>>>> is used, _m_a_p_m_e_m will append
               the output of _m_a_p_m_e_m to the existing contents of the
               specified file or device.  _F_i_l_e_s_p_e_c_s for redirection
               may not specify a password.

          ; _n_e_x_t _c_o_m_m_a_n_d
               After _m_a_p_m_e_m completes, the remainder of the command
               line is executed as a second command.  The command
               mmmmaaaappppmmmmeeeemmmm;;;;ttttiiiimmmmeeee will display memory information, and then
               the time will be displayed.

          <SHIFT>@
               When pressed during output to the display, the output
               will pause.  Pressing any other key resumes output.
               Pressing this key is ignored when output is redirected.





